cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the practical computational power of RNNs for language recognition. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the different variants of RNNs and their computational power. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RNNs are a popular tool in AI research, and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the limitations of RNNs with finite precision and linear computation time.
